Class SetMergeSortD

  • public class SetMergeSortD
extends SetMergeSort
    A merge sort operation on SortedTables with support for dealing with deletion entries. Like it's parent class, this models a data structure with no duplicates.

    Babak

    • Constructor Detail

      • SetMergeSortD

        public SetMergeSortD(SortedTable target,
             SortedTable[] sources,
             DeleteCodec deleteCodec,
             TableSet backSet)
              throws IOException
        Creates a new instance with the given delete codec and back-set. The delete codec encapsulates the protocol for delete overrides. The back-set determines whether or not any given delete entry in this merge should be preserved in the target of the merge.

        The number of rows in each source table's search buffer defaults to DEFAULT_ROWS_PER_SEARCH_BUFFER.

        Parameters:
        sources - the source tables ordered in increasing order of precedence. Each table contains unique rows (no 2 rows in a given table compare to 0 using the tables' row comparator). Results are very much undefined, o.w.
        deleteCodec - non-null delete codec
        backSet - optional back-set (may be null). Deletion entries in are checked against this back set in order to determine whether a given delete entry should purged (skipped) during the merge: if a given deletion entry overrides an entry in the back-set, then the deletion entry is preserved in the merge. Will typically be an of sub-type TableSetD.
        Throws:
        IOException

    • Method Detail

      • processTop

        protected void processTop()
                   throws IOException
        Description copied from class: BaseMergeSort
        Processes the top of the MergeSource stack. If any of the merge BaseMergeSort.sources is finished then that it should be removed from the sources list and placed in the BaseMergeSort.finishedSources list.

        Pre-condition

        • BaseMergeSort.sources is sorted
          • BaseMergeSort.sources has at least 2 elements

        Post-condition

        • BaseMergeSort.sources is sorted
          • BaseMergeSort.sources contains no finished instances.
        Overrides:
        processTop in class SetMergeSort
        Throws:
        IOException
